channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Biden Finally Speaks to Campus Chaos During Holocaust Remarks, but He Says One Thing While Doing Another
Johnson warned against making 'side deals' with GOP rebels: Don't 'grease a squeaky wheel'
item.description: House Republican lawmakers are calling on Speaker Mike Johnson to resist acquiescing to the demands of GOP rebels who are threatening to oust him.

item.title: Trump Scheduled for Graduation, Dinner on Same Day
item.description: It is going to be a busy May 17 for former President Donald Trump. Trump is scheduled to give the keynote address at the Minnesota Republican Party's annual Lincoln-Reagan Dinner on the same day he will be attending his son Barron's graduation from high school.

item.title: Mike Johnson Meets With Marjorie Taylor Greene to Hash Out Their Differences Amid Ouster Threats
Hamas sympathizers could be added to list that includes terrorist suspects if GOP bill becomes law
item.description: Legislation by a Republican senator would put terrorist supporters on the no-fly list, including if they had been disciplined for such conduct, in response to college protests.

item.title: Trump Mediating Rep. Greene, Speaker Johnson Impasse
item.description: Former President Donald Trump is not only making public statements in support of House Speaker Mike Johnson, R-La., but he is trying to mediate between the speaker and the Rep. Marjorie Taylor Greene, R-Ga., threat to file a notice to vacate.

item.title: WATCH: The Sidenote to the UNC-Chapel Hill Palestinian Flag Raising That Makes It So Much Worse
Chip Roy demands sanctions on ICC officials going after US, Israel
item.description: House GOP lawmakers are pushing for a new bill to force President Biden to sanction ICC officials who go after Americans or U.S. allies.

item.title: Bipartisan Bill Introduced to Recoup UNRWA Funds
item.description: Bipartisan members of Congress are seeking a refund on U.S. aid that was given to a controversial United Nations agency this year.

item.title: WATCH: The Tornadic Devastation of Barnsdall, Oklahoma, Drives Home the Importance of Weather Awareness
Flights for illegal immigrants without IDs targeted in FAA bill as deadline looms
item.description: GOP senators are looking to include a measure in the FAA reauthorization bill to stop illegal immigrants from flying without proper identification.

item.title: Biden Condemns Antisemitism at Holocaust Memorial
item.description: President Joe Biden on Tuesday warned that the threat of antisemitism is growing, in remarks honoring the 6 million Jews killed in the Holocaust, as his support for Israel's assault on Gaza divides his Democratic Party.

item.title: Bitter Man-Child David Hogg Announces 'One Thing Men Want,' Is Mocked Into Middle of Next Week
Eric Trump slams Stormy's testimony from front row court seat: 'Garbage'
item.description: Eric Trump, former President Donald Trump's son, slammed the Manhattan trial's testimony from former pornographic actress Stormy Daniels as "garbage."

item.title: Philadelphia Set to Clear Homeless Encampment, 'Drug Market'
item.description: Philadelphia will clear a homeless encampment Wednesday out of an area that is known as the center of the city's opioid crisis, a fulfillment of a campaign promise of recently elected Mayor Cherelle Parker.
